article.headline: Oakland, Mich. 84, UMKC 78
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. -- Keith Benson had a career-high 21 points and eight rebounds as Oakland, Mich. beat Missouri-Kansas City 84-78 on Thursday night. Erik Kangas added 19 points and Johnathon Jones scored 12 as the Golden Grizzlies (4-5, 1-1 Summit League) gave coach Greg Kampe his 400th career victory. Dane Brumagin led UMKC (3-6, 1-1) with 29 points, including a pair of free throws with 1:11 left in the game that gave the Kangaroos their only lead of the second half at 77-76. But Kangas connected on a 3-pointer 19 seconds later that put Oakland back on top for good at 79-77. UMKC won the rebounding battle 44-36 but was outscored inside 42-17 by the taller Grizzlies. Spencer Johnson added 20 points and 13 rebounds and Reggie Hamilton scored 15 for the Roos.
